cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper is about using text mining tools and machine learning models to learn vector representations of biological concepts mentioned in PubMed abstracts. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category of computer science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the use of machine learning models and embeddings suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the embeddings on multiple bioinformatics tasks suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of embeddings and deep learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to the deep learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
